A widow, Mrs. Toyin Olusa, has been sentenced to one year imprisonment for causing the death of her husband, Mr Adeyinka Olusa. Mrs. Olusa was said to have deliberately poured hot water on her husband, thereby causing him bodily harm, particularly to his mouth, chest, hands, thighs and legs. The incident was said to occurred at Ijoka area of Akure. Her husband, a former auditor at the School of Health Technology, Akure died at the University College Hospital, Ibadan, Oyo State in 2017. Mrs. Olusa was arrested by the husbandâ€™s family who accused her of pouring hot water on him. Magistrate, Mrs Ruth Olomilua however gave her an option of fine of N200,000.